(Lesson Vocabulary) Tj
T*
(- Reproduction: The main topic being studied, understood here as reproduction ensures) Tj
T*
(the continuation of species.) Tj
T*
(- Core Focus: The main idea the learner must understand in this lesson: sexual) Tj
T*
(reproduction, fertilization, and development.) Tj
T*
(- Application: The point where the explanation is used in practice, such as comparing) Tj
T*
(male and female reproductive roles.) Tj
T*
(- Common Error: A repeated learner difficulty in this topic, for example mixing) Tj
T*
(fertilization with implantation or growth stages.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Common Mistakes) Tj
T*
(- Misunderstanding the core focus of Reproduction: sexual reproduction, fertilization,) Tj
T*
(and development.) Tj
T*
(- Mixing fertilization with implantation or growth stages.) Tj
T*
(- Jumping to an answer without showing the steps or reasoning clearly.) Tj
T*
(- Practising Reproduction without checking whether the method matches the question being) Tj
T*
(asked.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
